# Component Preferences

- Use Mantine components over custom CSS (per global rules)
- Use `SegmentedControl` over `Select`/dropdowns when options are few and discrete
  - Saves space and reduces clicks
  - Good for: severity levels, toggle options, view modes
- Use `@mantine/form` with `useForm` hook for form state and validation

# Theme Usage

- Access theme via `useMantineTheme()` hook for colors and spacing
- Use `theme.colors.[color][shade]` for consistent coloring (e.g., `theme.colors.green[7]`)
- Prefer theme colors over hardcoded hex values

# Common Packages

- `@mantine/core` - Core components (Button, Card, Text, etc.)
- `@mantine/hooks` - Utility hooks (useDisclosure, useFullscreen, etc.)
- `@mantine/form` - Form state management and validation
- `@mantine/notifications` - Toast notifications
- `@mantine/dates` - Date/time pickers with dayjs
- `@mantine/dropzone` - File upload dropzone
- `@mantine/spotlight` - Command palette / search

# Styling

- Use Mantine's style props (p, m, c, bg, etc.) over inline styles
- Use `rem()` function for consistent sizing
- Use `@mantine/core` Stack/Group for layout instead of custom flexbox
